            <biogHist>
                <abstract>Metropolitan bp. of Mabbug (modern Membij/ancient Hierapolis) (485-519),
                    ascetic theologian, christological polemicist, and sponsor of the Philoxenian
                    NT.</abstract>
                <p>Longer Description Here</p>
                <chronList>
                    <chronItem>
                        <date standardDate="0484">484</date>
                        <placeEntry vocabularySource="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/520998"
                            >Constantinople</placeEntry>
                        <event>Supporting the Henotikon, Philoxenos visited Constantinople in 484
                            to offer Zeno a Miaphysite profession of faith.</event>


                    </chronItem>
                    <chronItem>
                        <date standardDate="0486">486</date>
                        <placeEntry vocabularySource="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/658480"
                            >Mabbug ܡܒܘܓ</placeEntry>
                        <event>After the restoration of Peter the Fuller as patriarch of Antioch,
                            Philoxenos was named metropolitan of Mabbug.</event>


                    </chronItem>
                    <chronItem>
                        <date standardDate="0512">512</date>
                        <placeEntry vocabularySource="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/658381"
                            >Antioch ܐܢܛܝܘܟܝܐ</placeEntry>
                        <event>Philoxenos’s anti-Chalcedon efforts culminated in 512 when Flavian
                            was ousted in favor of Severus as Patr. of Antioch. Philoxenos and his
                            suffragan bishops (including a relation, Philoxenos of Doliche) assisted
                            at Severus’s consecration. </event>


                    </chronItem>
                    <chronItem>
                        <date standardDate="0519">519</date>
                        <placeEntry vocabularySource="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/844926"
                            >Gangra</placeEntry>
                        <event>In 519, Justin I exiled Philoxenos. In his final years, Philoxenos
                            continued writing to monastic communities, encouraging them to persist
                            in ascesis and Miaphysite christology.</event>


                    </chronItem>
                    <chronItem>
                        <date standardDate="0523">523</date>
                        <placeEntry vocabularySource="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/216927"
                            >Philippopolis/Trimontium</placeEntry>
                        <event>Philoxenos died in 523 under house arrest. Later traditions that he
                            was executed are difficult to substantiate.</event>

                    </chronItem>
                </chronList>
            </biogHist>
